  "upgrade_suggestion": "No audiophile pressing of Boyz II Men II has been issued. The 2016 UMe reissue you own is the only modern domestic vinyl configuration. Original 1994 Motown pressings (r77912) are the alternative, though no mastering advantage over the reissue has been documented.",
  "commentary": "**II** is the second studio album by Boyz II Men, released on **Motown Records** in August 1994. Produced primarily by **Jimmy Jam and Terry Lewis** (Flyte Tyme Productions) and **Babyface** (ECAF Productions), it arrived on the back of the group's breakthrough with *Cooleyhighharmony* and the smash single \"End of the Road.\" *II* became one of the best-selling R&B albums of the 1990s, propelled by two singles that each broke the record for longest run at number one on the Billboard Hot 100 at the time of their chart peaks: **\"I'll Make Love To You\"** (14 weeks) and **\"On Bended Knee\"** (6 weeks, displacing \"I'll Make Love To You\" from the top spot — making Boyz II Men the first act to replace themselves at number one since The Beatles). The album sold over 12 million copies in the US and won two Grammy Awards.\n\nThe **2016 reissue** was released by **Motown Records / Universal Music Enterprises** under catalog **B0025089-01**, distributed by Universal Music Distribution. It was pressed as a **2×LP** on standard black vinyl, making it the more common domestic variant of this reissue (a companion blue vinyl pressing, r18261367, was issued simultaneously). The pressing plant is not explicitly identified on the release, but the `S-97847` stamper code in the deadwax is consistent with UMe's domestic pressing suppliers during this period. The `B-0025089-01A` deadwax inscription mirrors the catalog number with a side designation suffix.\n\nThe 14-track sequence across four sides spreads the album's content evenly, with the two signature ballads appearing on Side C (\"I'll Make Love To You\") and Side D (\"On Bended Knee\") — a configuration that mirrors their original album sequence and places the commercial centerpieces on the second disc.\n\n**About this 2016 US pressing (2×LP, black vinyl):** Motown Records / Universal Music Enterprises catalog **B0025089-01** (barcode **602547924339**), black vinyl. Deadwax: `S-97847` / `B-0025089-01A`. Standard black vinyl variant; blue vinyl sibling is r18261367.\n\n### Gemini Notes\n\nReleased in 1994, *II* is the monumental sophomore album from R&B legends Boyz II Men. Featuring production from Babyface and Jimmy Jam & Terry Lewis, the album spawned massive hits like \"I'll Make Love to You\" and \"On Bended Knee,\" defining the sound of 90s R&B.\n\n**About this pressing:**",
